            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Manual Data Extraction</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Invoices, contracts, applications arrive as PDFs. Someone manually reads them, extracts structured data, enters it into systems. Slow, error-prone, and doesn't scale.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Inconsistent Decision-Making</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Leads scored by intuition. Accuracy depends on who does it. Approvals decided by gut feel. Same requests get different outcomes. Patterns invisible because decisions aren't systematic.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">No Early Warning System</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Problems emerge late. Customer churn discovered after they're gone. Project timeline slips at deadline. Market shifts discovered after you've lost ground. No systematic pattern detection.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Scaling Requires Headcount</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                As volume grows, you hire more people to handle same tasks. Document processing needs another person. Lead scoring needs another person. No leverage, just multiplication.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Column: What Changes After Deployment -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-12">What Changes After Deployment</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Automatic Data Extraction</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Documents arrive, structured data extracted automatically, validated for accuracy, ready for use. Manual data entry eliminated. Accuracy improves over time.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Systematic Decision-Making</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                AI applies same logic consistently. Lead scoring uses explicit criteria, not gut. Approvals evaluated against historical data. Decisions are repeatable and measurable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Proactive Pattern Detection</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                System continuously monitors operations and surfaces patterns you wouldn't see manually. Churn risk detected early. Timeline slips detected before crisis. Market shifts visible in data.
              </p>
