        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Extraction & Understanding</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            For documents: What type is this? What's important in it? Are there issues (duplicates, unusual terms, missing info)? How does it compare to historical documents? The system reads and understands automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Pattern Analysis</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            What patterns predict success? Which leads close? Which customers churn? Which projects slip? What's abnormal? What correlations exist? The system identifies patterns in historical data automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Scoring & Recommendation</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            The system scores quality, risk, and priority. Lead quality score: likelihood to close and deal value. Customer health score: churn risk, expansion opportunity. Document risk: unusual terms, policy violations. Then generates recommendations: next best action, decision context, risk flagging.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Human Decision Layer</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            AI makes recommendations. Humans make decisions. Low-confidence extractions get human review. High-risk decisions go to specialists. Unusual patterns escalate. Feedback loop: human corrections improve the AI over time.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 6: THIS ACTUALLY WORKS -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
